rlm-dbt-sandbox

Create your personal dbt sandbox BigQuery datasets.

For each layer L listed in DBT_SANDBOX_LAYERS, creates the dataset
<DBT_DATASET_PREFIX>_<L> inside DBT_DEV_PROJECT. Each dataset is
labelled sandbox:true and given a default table expiration of 30
days. Datasets that already exist are skipped (idempotent).

DBT_DEV_PROJECT must not end in -prod; the function refuses to run
otherwise as a guard against accidentally polluting production.

ENVIRONMENT
  DBT_DATASET_PREFIX   Required. Prefix for sandbox datasets,
                       typically your username (e.g. ecerulm).
  DBT_DEV_PROJECT      Required. Target BigQuery project. Must not
                       end in -prod.
  DBT_SANDBOX_LAYERS   Required. Colon-separated list of layer
                       suffixes (e.g. prep:psa:dw:rd). Each
                       produces dataset <prefix>_<layer>.

REQUIRES
  bq (Google Cloud SDK)

EXAMPLES
  dbt-sandbox
